<HEADLINE>
<P>
STEP RIGHT IN TO FOLK DANCING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Zan Dubin's otherwise excellent article on folk dancing (cover story, Feb. 10) 
could needlessly discourage new folks from joining in, for two reasons. 
</P>
<P>
 First, don't stay away because you have nothing to wear. At least with 
international folk dancing, adequate attire is a T-shirt and slacks for most 
events. Don't let the photos give you pause. 
</P>
<P>
 Second, your eyes are not likely to glaze over. Anyone with a reasonable 
measure of coordination and presence of mind will do just fine. 
</P>
<P>
 The only advisable optional equipment is a sense of humor. 
</P>
<P>
 WILLIAM J. EVANS 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 
</P>
