<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLINTON WELFARE CUTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * By advocating the taxing of food stamps and the cutting of welfare and SSI 
benefits, President Clinton has forsaken the roots and basic principles of the 
Democratic Party. For many decades the Democrats have been the party of 
compassion and the defender of the little guy and the downtrodden. 
</P>
<P>
 The best way to help the poor is the creation of jobs, even if they are the 
WPA-CCC-type jobs that President Roosevelt implemented. As many other counties 
do, we could put in a value-added tax where the burden is spread to everyone. 
If he wants to cut welfare, why doesn't he cut welfare for the affluent, such 
as the subsidy to the wool and mohair producers, which has been in place since 
the Korean War. 
</P>
<P>
 Must we once again dump on the poor, handicapped and elderly? 
</P>
<P>
 TERRY L. MALONE 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 
</P>
</TEXT>
