<LENGTH>
<P>
137 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAT SHOW TO HELP DISPLACED PETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Animal shelters are filled to capacity with hundreds of pets lost or left 
homeless following the January earthquake. So the California State Humane 
Officers and the American Cat Assn. will combine efforts to offer cat adoptions 
in conjunction with the Championship Cat Show this weekend at the LAX 
Hilton.Admission to the "Animal Rescue and Orphan Adoption & Championship Cat 
Competition" Saturday and Sunday will help pay for the upkeep of homeless or 
injured pets. The competition will feature hundreds of cats and kittens, from 
Siamese to Scottish Folds, competing for the top cat title. There is also a 
division for household cats. The show takes place at the Airport Hilton, 5711 
W. Century Blvd., Los Angeles. 9 a.m.-5 p.m. Donation $5; $4 children. For 
information, call (818) 780-0001. LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
