<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIVISIONS I AND II; BUENA BEATS CAPISTRANO VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley Coach Pete Belanto watched two tapes of top-seeded Ventura 
Buena before his team lost to the Bulldogs, 51-37, in a Southern Section 
Division I-A girls' basketball quarterfinals Wednesday at Capistrano Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 "They are all talent," Belanto said."(Coach Joe Vaughan) hasn't got 450 wins 
without some talent." 
</P>
<P>
 The Bulldogs showed some of that talent, making few mistakes and hitting shots 
from all over the court, including 10 of 12 from the free-throw line. 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley (14-14) kept it close in the first half, down 25-18 and 
outrebounding Buena, 13-11. Jennifer Garrett had seven boards at the half, 
finishing with 12. 
</P>
<P>
 "I thought we played better than them," Belanto said. "Jen got a lot of 
rebounds, but she couldn't put them back in." 
</P>
<P>
 The third quarter was all Buena (22-2). The Bulldogs put on the pressure, 
causing four consecutive Cougar turnovers and sparking a 14-2 run ending the 
third quarter up 42-24. 
</P>
<P>
 Susan Scott, who has led Capistrano Valley in the playoffs averaging 26 
points, was held to 10, only one in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Katie Scott led the Cougars with 12. 
</P>
<P>
 "They are a great team, nobody is going to beat them," Belanto said. "It was 
no disgrace losing to them." 
</P>
<P>
 Michelle Giordano had a game-high 21 points for Buena. MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA022494-0057 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 016631 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
