<P>
ESTANCIA UPSETS VAQUEROS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI, Special To The Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Reserve Cyndi Richards made six of seven shots to help Estancia to a 51-44 
victory over third-seeded Rancho Alamitos in a Southern Section Division III-A 
girls' basketball quarterfinal Wednesday at Estancia. 
</P>
<P>
 "We asked her to come in and play defense and rebound and she did both besides 
scoring," said Rich Boyce, Estancia's acting coach. 
</P>
<P>
 Estancia will paly San Luis Obispo, which upset second-seeded Ojai Nordhoff, 
in a semifinal Saturday at a site to be determined by Estancia. 
</P>
<P>
 Richards scored consecutive baskets late in he first quarter, giving the 
Eagles an 8-5 lead. They never trailed after that. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos (20-7) tied the score, 14-14, with 5:11 left in the second 
quarter before Estancia pulled away. Jessica Waltz's steal and layup with one 
second left gave Estancia a 24-18 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Estancia's Laura Czingula had 17 points and 10 rebounds. 
</P>
