<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEMBROKE POSTS $29.40 UPSET IN U.S DEBUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pembroke, who had campaigned in Britain, won his U.S. debut Wednesday, coming 
from just off the pace to win the $64,400 turf feature at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
 A 14-1 shot ridden by Alex Solis, Pembroke finished one length in front of 
D'Hallevant, with Portoferraio another 3 1/2 lengths behind.Didyme, the 2-1 
favorite, finished fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 Pembroke, a 4-year-old Kentucky-bred colt by Gone West, carried 114 pounds and 
was clocked in 1:13 3-5 for the 6 1/2 furlongs. 
</P>
<P>
 The winner paid $29.40, $12.40 and $8. D'Hallevant, ridden by Corey Nakatani 
and carrying 113, paid $5.80 and $4.40. Portoferraio, an Argentine-bred runner 
ridden by Pat Valenzuela and carrying 121, paid $6.80. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the fourth win in nine career starts for Pembroke. 
</P>
</TEXT>
