<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; SANDERS' 44 POINTS OVERWHELM MONROE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Franklin High's Johnny Sanders erupted for 44 points and Monroe failed to make 
two jump shots in the final seconds as Franklin won, 83-82, in the first round 
of the City Section 3-A Division boys' basketball playoffs Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
 One-point losses have eliminated Monroe two years in a row. The Vikings 
(10-13) lost to Banning, 60-59, in the final last season. 
</P>
<P>
 Sanders, who made three three-point shots, scored 14 of the Panthers' 20 
points in the first quarter and 13 of their 22 in the third. 
</P>
<P>
 But Monroe led, 82-79, before Johnny Redford hit a three-pointer to tie the 
score with 50 seconds to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Monroe ran the clock down but a 17-foot jump shot was missed with 12 seconds 
to play. 
</P>
<P>
 The shot bounced off the rim, Sanders grabbed the rebound and was fouled 
attempting a layup at the other end with 3.5 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 Sanders made the first shot and missed the second. 
</P>
<P>
 Kenyatta Niles and Shaka Stiner each scored 16 points for Monroe. 
</P>
<P>
 Franklin made eight of 14 free throws, and Monroe attempted only three. 
</P>
<P>
 Fairfax 61, Grant 48 -- Shapigan Roberts had 18 points and the Lions 
out-rebounded Grant, 28-17, in a City 4-A first-round game at Grant. 
</P>
<P>
 Shawn Hackett led the Lancers (18-6) with 13 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Grant scored only 13 points in the second and third quarters combined. GIRLS' 
BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany 61, Valencia 30 -- Kelly McKay scored the first 12 points of the game 
and had six of Alemany's 30 steals, leading the Indians (25-0) in a Division 
II-A second round game at Placentia. 
</P>
<P>
 McKay finished with 16 points. Carly Funicello led the Indians with 20 points 
and Samantha Rigley scored 18. 
