<HEADLINE>
<P>
HUGHES PACES NORTHRIDGE'S SWEEP OF IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Freshman Jason Hughes had 19 kills and junior Peter Piexoto added 10 as Cal 
State Northridge defeated UC Irvine, 15-8, 15-4, 15-6, in a Mountain Pacific 
Sports Federation men's volleyball match Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory was the fourth in a row for Northridge (6-3, 2-1 in conference), 
which received nine kills apiece from Oliver Heitman and Collin Smith. 
</P>
<P>
 The Matadors, runners-up in last year's NCAA championships, had a .385 hitting 
percentage, including a .461 mark in game three. 
</P>
<P>
 Hughes hit .533 and Heitman hit .529 for Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
 Gary Reznick had 37 assists for the Matadors and tied Piexoto for a match-high 
honors with six digs. 
</P>
<P>
 Heitman, Hughes, Piexoto and Craig Hewitt each had three blocks for 
Northridge, which improved its series record to 15-2 against the Anteaters. 
</P>
<P>
 Evan Alexander had 10 kills for UC Irvine (1-9, 1-8), which hit .126 overall 
and .000 in the second and third games. 
</P>
