<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: LYNWOOD; CONSTRUCTION PLANS FOR BIRTHING CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Construction of an $18.8-million birthing center at St. Francis Medical Center 
will begin in September, hospital officials announced last week. 
</P>
<P>
 The center will have one an operating suite for post-delivery surgical 
procedures, 20 regular delivery rooms, two Cesarean delivery rooms, 72 beds and 
a nursery for 40 babies. It is expected to be completed by the end of 1996. 
</P>
<P>
 Funding for the 69,000-square-foot center comes from tax-exempt state bonds. 
</P>
