<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS; LOS ANGELES; AIRPORT BEGINS ELECTRIC SHUTTLE BUS SERVICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles International Airport last week introduced the first of four 
electric shuttle buses for the regular route between remote parking lots and 
the main terminal. 
</P>
<P>
 The battery-powered buses emit 97% less pollution than diesel-powered vehicles 
and can carry 25 seated and seven standing passengers, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Use of the one bus will eliminate more than 5,000 pounds of smog-forming 
emissions from the atmosphere this year, Los Angeles City Councilwoman Ruth 
Galanter said. Three buses are scheduled to be added later this year. SUSAN 
WOODWARD 
</P>
