<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRIME: TEACHER IS VICTIMIZED TWICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On Feb. 10 at 9:50 a.m., Washington Middle School teacher Pamela Altea 
cautioned two adults to leave the area adjacent to the Pasadena school. With a 
group of students watching, the adults viciously attacked Altea and beat her to 
a state of near senselessness. 
</P>
<P>
 It appears that school board President George Van Alstine, Supt. Vera Vignes, 
district Police Chief Jarado J. Blue, Principal Karen Kommer and United 
Teachers of Pasadena President Frank Scoonover all agree that the beating was 
the teacher's fault because she did not lock a gate. 
</P>
<P>
 It seems Pamela Altea is not only a victim of a criminal beating but of a 
school system that is managed by a bureaucracy that is more interested in job 
security and the next promotion than in meeting the education needs of the 
community. 
</P>
<P>
 BOB LOW 
</P>
<P>
 Covina  
</P>
