<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: WEST HOLLYWOOD; BUILDING FEES WAIVED AS PART OF QUAKE RELIEF 
EFFORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is waiving fees on inspections or repairs to earthquake-damaged 
buildings and offering damaged businesses a penalty-free extension on paying 
the business tax. 
</P>
<P>
 The city's earthquake relief program also waives for 30 days a city tax on 
hotel rooms for people who work in West Hollywood and were displaced from their 
homes. 
</P>
<P>
 Inspection and building fees were waived for quake-affected businesses that 
wish to relocate to West Hollywood. The relief plan will be in place until May 
17. 
</P>
<P>
 Earthquake damage in West Hollywood was minimal, with only a handful of 
buildings deemed unsafe. 
</P>
<P>
 But many structures had broken windows, ruptured water heaters and other 
similar problems. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (310) 854-7475. 
</P>
</TEXT>
