<HEADLINE>
<P>
TEENS / SEEN AT SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Staying contemporary is important to Michelle Cheun, 16, of Arcadia High 
School. 
</P>
<P>
 Clothes: "I usually buy Gap, J. Crew or Wet Seal. I just want to follow, like, 
new fashion. I look at magazines and see what is new fashion for this month." 
</P>
<P>
 Shoes: "These are Dockers. I just like boy-style, army-style." 
</P>
<P>
 Accessories: In accessories, Michelle also tries to sport the newest fashion. 
"I just like huge, so that everyone can see it." Hair is also an important part 
of the look: "My hair is usually curly, but this morning I blew it dry so that 
it'd go with this outfit." 
</P>
</TEXT>
