<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAW ENFORCEMENT: A TRIBUTE TO SLAIN OFFICERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On Feb. 14, we were all shocked and appalled to learn of the deaths of Capt. 
Michael Tracy and Sgt. Tom Vanderpool of the Palos Verdes Estates Police 
Department. Over the years, Peninsula residents have come to know and respect 
the members of the department as well as the other uniformed police officers 
who serve us well.These men and women put their lives on the line on a daily 
basis to protect and serve the members of our community and schools. 
</P>
<P>
 A senseless killing such as this serves to remind us of how precious human 
life is and also how fragile it can be. Their dedication will always be 
remembered. 
</P>
<P>
 Our hearts go out to the families and friends of these brave and wonderful 
men. The Palos Verdes Peninsula Unified School District, its board, teachers, 
staff and students will always be indebted to these courageous men. 
</P>
<P>
 JOAN DAVIDSON 
</P>
<P>
 MICHAEL W. CASTON 
</P>
<P>
 Davidson is president of the Palos Verdes Peninsula Board of Education. Caston 
is superintendent of schools.  
</P>
</TEXT>
