<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: NOT UNTIL YOU FINISH YOUR OREOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nabisco Biscuit Co. said it will introduce by the end of the year six new 
breakfast snacks, including cereal bars based on Oreos. 
</P>
<P>
 The new items include Oreo, Chips Ahoy and Nutter Butter granola bars, along 
with fat-free cereal bars, said the unit of RJR Nabisco Holdings Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said 24% of all snacking is done in the morning, more than double 
the level of 10 years ago. 
</P>
<P>
 "Time-pinched commuters who eat in their cars or on public transit on the way 
to work are major morning snackers, as are teens," said Sharon Fordham, Nabisco 
vice president of new business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
