<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUAKE DIRECTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by David E. Brady and Stephanie Stassel. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Editor's note: All information subject to change. Call ahead whenever 
possible. * FEMA Disaster Hot Line 
</P>
<P>
 (800) 525-0321 
</P>
<P>
 (800) 660-8005 TDD 
</P>
<P>
 * FEMA 24-Hour Registration Line 
</P>
<P>
 (800) 462-9029 
</P>
<P>
 (800) 462-7585 TDD 
</P>
<P>
 The Federal Emergency Management Agency is operating several local Disaster 
Aid Centers and Earthquake Service Centers. Programs are being offered to cover 
earthquake losses to residences, personal property and businesses not covered 
by insurance or other aid programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Registrants can apply for financial assistance at any center or call the 
registration line. Be prepared to provide your name, address, Social Security 
number and those of other occupants in the house at the time of the quake. 
Centers are open 9 a.m. to 7 p.m. Monday through Saturday. For locations, call 
the FEMA disaster hot line. 
</P>
<P>
 * Red Cross Hot Line 
</P>
<P>
 (213) 739-4543 
</P>
<P>
 The Red Cross is operating several local service centers that offer vouchers 
for food, clothing, temporary housing/rental assistance, help with 
health/medical needs, urgent household items and some home repairs. Centers are 
open 9 a.m. to 7 p.m. daily. For locations, call the Red Cross hot line. 
</P>
<P>
 * Salvation Army 24-Hour Hot Line 
</P>
<P>
 (800) 725-9005 
</P>
<P>
 The Salvation Army is operating three community services centers 9 a.m. to 5 
p.m. Monday through Saturday. Quake victims in the following areas may call for 
an appointment for assistance. 
</P>
