<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' SWIMMING AND DIVING '94 / SIX TEAMS TO WATCH; IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coach: Scott Hinman (ninth year). 
</P>
<P>
 1993: Sea View League champion; third at Division II championship meet. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Taryn Beard, Sr.; Lauren Henne, Jr.; Alice Huszcz, Jr.; Monica 
Huszcz, Sr.; Melissa Lloyd, So., diving; Wendy O'Brien, Jr.; Molly Zak, Jr. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomers: Amy Aldinger, Fr.; Lana Kraus, Fr.; Erin Rollins, Fr.; Debbie 
Wold, Fr. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: Irvine was impressive in its Sea View League debut last year, winning 
the title. This season, "barring disaster, we'll win, place or show," Hinman 
said in reference to the team's chances in league and at the section meet. 
Irvine boasts only one senior, Monica Huszcz, and the Vaqueros lack the 
power-packed names, but they can creep up on you. Their relays are lethal. 
Irvine finished second in the 400-yard free relay and seventh in the 200 medley 
and return three swimmers from each. Traditionally, Irvine has faltered in 
qualifying individuals for the championship meet, but Hinman believes that's a 
problem of the past. 
</P>
</TEXT>
