<P>
LILLEHAMMER / '94 WINTER OLYMPICS; NOTEBOOK; SHIMER AND WILL TO REPRESENT U.S. 
IN FOUR-MAN SLEDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROSS NEWHAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Randy Will and Brian Shimer won the two U.S. berths in the four-man bobsled 
competition Saturday and Sunday as Jim Herberich was eliminated in a two-heat 
race-off.Shimer came from behind in the second heat to edge Herberich by 
two-hundredths of a second. Shimer's 52.53 seconds on that run was the second 
fastest in a field of 34 sleds. Will had the field's second-fastest run in the 
first heat, 52.01. 
</P>
<P>
 "I let out a big sigh of relief," the veteran Shimer said of his near 
elimination. "I thought my time was really slow. I was having flashes all the 
way down. I surprised myself." ROSS NEWHAN 
