<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: CSUN VOLLEYBALL AIDES NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lian Kang Lu, Cal State Northridge's new women's volleyball coach, completed 
his staff on Wednesday, announcing the hiring of assistants Carolyn Hueth and 
Maria Reyes-Sanchez. 
</P>
<P>
 Hueth, 23, Lu's top assistant, was an assistant coach at Mira Costa High the 
past two seasons. She was a four-year starter at Pepperdine, a three-time team 
captain and the West Coast Conference player of the year in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 Reyes-Sanchez, 24, was team captain at UC Santa Barbara in 1990-91 when Lu was 
an assistant coach there.  
</P>
<P>
 She was the team's most valuable player and an All-American selection in 1991. 
Reyes-Sanchez is UCSB's all-time leader in digs and service aces. Football 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge's football recruiting class reached six on Wednesday when Coach Bob 
Burt announced that Virgil Nelson and Anthony Fernandez, defensive linemen from 
Citrus College, have signed NCAA letters of intent. 
</P>
<P>
 Nelson, 6-2, 250, is expected to play defensive end. 
</P>
<P>
 Fernandez, 6-4, 257, will play tackle. 
</P>
<P>
 "They give us solid depth at that position," Burt said. "They're solid, 
mature-type people." 
</P>
<P>
 The Matadors have defensive line starters Oscar Wilson, Chris Smith and Tim 
Gardner returning next fall. Baseball 
</P>
<P>
 The Chatsworth High baseball team has scheduled its annual alumni game for 
Sunday at 11 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Former players interested in playing are encouraged to contact Coach Tom 
Meusborn at 818-341-6211. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Genevieve High has scheduled its alumni baseball game for March 5 at the 
Mission College field at El Cariso Park in Sylmar. Game time is 11 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Former players interested in playing are encouraged to contact Athletic 
Director Richard Fong at 818-894-6417, ext. 32. Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 Rupert Sapwell is a junior in athletic eligibility, but this will be his final 
season at Cal Lutheran. He expects to graduate in May before starting his 
career in the National Basketball League in his native Australia later this 
year. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's very, very intelligent," Coach Mike Dunlap said. "He has just torn 
through the academic schedule here. He has something like a 3.8 average." 
</P>
<P>
 Sapwell, a 6-6, 220-pound forward, is averaging 11.7 points and 6.6 rebounds, 
and ranks 17th on Cal Lutheran's career rebounding list with 402. 
</P>
<P>
 Emeka Okenwa has moved to 12th on The Master's career rebounding list with 
577. Okenwa has averaged 9.8 rebounds a game during his two seasons at the 
school. 
</P>
