<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: ADVERTISING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Anne Michaud, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 First Client a Big One: Joel Don, formerly the spokesman for computer maker 
AST Research Inc. in Irvine, has opened the doors to his own firm, 
Communication Perspectives Inc., in Rancho Santa Margarita. 
</P>
<P>
 His first client: Rockwell International in Newport Beach.Don said he will 
work with the company's developing digital communications division, which 
handles such products as packet radio and wireless communications. 
</P>
<P>
 Don said he is now formally a member of the virtual corporation, working with 
clients as they need it. That used to be called free-lancing, and it used to be 
a temporary condition. But Don said he's in this for the long run. 
</P>
<P>
 "The marketplace has shifted to outsourcing," he said. "A lot of companies 
have downsized, and they are looking for strategic partnerships with other 
entrepreneurial companies." 
</P>
