<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION WRESTLING; CALVARY CHAPEL, EL MODENA ATTEMPT TO ADD TO THEIR 
COLLECTION OF TITLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIM Q. BERKSHIRE, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel and El Modena, two wrestling teams on a roll, will attempt to 
pick up their second Southern Section championships in six days tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 The Division I and III dual meet wrestling finals will be contested at El 
Modena and Calvary Chapel, on the heels of the Vanguards' and Eagles' titles in 
the individual championships Saturday.It was the fourth consecutive team title 
for Calvary Chapel and the first for El Modena, the top two teams in the county 
all season. 
</P>
<P>
 Century League champion El Modena, which finished second in the individual 
meet and dual Division I championships last year, will meet Channel League 
champion Ventura, runner-up to the Vanguards at Saturday's meet. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, before losing to Indio in the final, El Modena defeated Ventura, 
39-18, in the dual quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura, strongest at the lighter and heavier weights, has an individual 
champion in heavyweight Sean Burdick, and a runner-up in Ryan Atherton at 103 
pounds. 
</P>
<P>
 El Modena is packed with talent in the middle classes. Teak Sato (130) and 
Juan Alvarez (135) won championships and David Wells (140) was a finalist. At 
140, the match between Wells and Ventura's Chris Karlowsky should be a 
highlight of the meet. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills, recent winner of its seventh consecutive Pacific Coast League 
title, meets defending State champion Calvary Chapel. The Eagles' feature five 
two-time Division III section champions in Shane Valdez, Dane Valdez, Mauricio 
Mor, Josh Holiday and Ed Mosely and runner-ups Joe Calavitta, Danny Robinson 
and Matt Van Hook. 
</P>
