<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: OC HIGH / STUDENT NEWS & VIEWS; SPIRITED DEBATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 School spirit lagging? At Villa Park High School, enthusiastic students can 
win Spartan spirit bucks by cheering at assemblies and games, participating in 
spirit competitions, wearing Spartan paraphernalia and taking part in spirit 
weeks, the student newspaper, the Oracle, reports. 
</P>
<P>
 The bucks can be used at periodic auctions for gift certificates, movie 
passes, tapes, videos and food.  
</P>
<P>
 The ASB is encouraged by the results, but reaction has been mixed. "I don't 
think you should have to bribe people to be spirited," said one student. "It's 
kind of sad that we have to reward students for showing spirit, but it's 
working," said another. "There are not enough opportunities to earn spirit 
bucks," complains another. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA022494-0331 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 016905 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
February 24, 1994, Thursday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
