INSIDE LINE: NOT PLAYING; OC HIGH / STUDENT NEWS & VIEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A a play based on the comic strip "Li'l Abner" was canceled at a high school 
in New Hampshire after several female students complained it was sexist. 
</P>
<P>
 "We do not want to be on stage exploited, demeaned and degraded," said student 
Robin Bartlett. Bartlett said students were uneasy about dialogue that 
included: 
</P>
<P>
 * Daisy Mae singing: "My aim in life is to be a good wife." 
</P>
<P>
 * Earthquake Magoon saying to another man: "What's your pleasure? But I see 
you've already brought it (a woman) with you." 
</P>
</TEXT>
