<HEADLINE>
<P>
SERVICES FOR OFFICER SCHEDULED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A memorial service is scheduled Monday for Christy Lynne Hamilton, the rookie 
Los Angeles Police Department officer who was killed responding to a domestic 
disturbance call earlier this week. She was the LAPD's second female officer to 
die in the line of duty. 
</P>
<P>
 Hamilton, 45, who graduated from the Police Academy last Friday, died early 
Tuesday after she was shot in Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
 A viewing is planned from 4 to 9 p.m. Sunday at Forest Lawn's Hollywood Hills 
mortuary, 6300 Forest Lawn Drive, Los Angeles. A memorial service will be held 
Monday at 10:30 a.m. at Grace Community Church of the Valley, 13248 Roscoe 
Blvd., Sun Valley. Burial will follow at Forest Lawn Memorial-Park, Hollywood 
Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 In lieu of flowers, memorial donations may be made to a fund in Hamilton's 
name in care of the LAPD's Employee Assistance Unit, Medical Liaison Section, 
150 N. Los Angeles St., Room 818, Los Angeles 90012. 
</P>
</TEXT>
