<TEXT>
<P>
 Maria Guarnaschelli, perhaps the most successful cookbook editor of the last 
10 years, is changing houses, going from William Morrow to Simon and Schuster. 
The editor behind talents as varied as Jeff "The Frugal Gourmet" Smith, "The 
Cake Bible" author Rose Levy Beranbaum, and French cooking expert Patricia 
Wells, Guarnaschelli's future has been a much-discussed topic lately in 
publishing circles. At press time, it was not known which authors would 
accompany her to her new post. RUSS PARSONS 
</P>
